The `isNearlyEqual` function is defined as an extension on the `FloatingPoint` protocol (lines 25-28), which means it's available on all floating-point types including `Double`, `Float`, `CGFloat`, etc. It compares two floating-point numbers by checking if their absolute difference is less than or equal to the unit in the last place (`.ulpOfOne`).
